---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Interview Transcription Software — Private, Free, No Upload | AudioSRT" description="Transcribe interviews privately and for free. Your audio never leaves your device, ideal for sensitive source material and confidential conversations." canonical="https://audiosrt.com/tools/interview-transcription">
  <Header />
  <main class="lp-main">

    <section class="lp-hero">
      <span class="lp-badge">Zero Upload · Source Confidentiality</span>
      <h1 class="lp-h1">Interview Transcription Software<br><span class="lp-accent">Free and Private</span></h1>
      <p class="lp-intro">
        For journalists, UX researchers, HR professionals, and qualitative researchers, the interview recording is often the most sensitive file in a project. Uploading it to a cloud transcription service creates a copy of that recording outside your control — on infrastructure you don't own, governed by privacy policies you may not have read. AudioSRT processes every file locally, entirely within your browser. Nothing is sent anywhere.
      </p>
      <p class="lp-intro">
        Whisper handles conversational speech well — accented speakers, overlapping voices, informal language, and the crosstalk that characterizes real interviews rather than scripted content. After transcription, you can clean up filler words and false starts directly in the editor before you export, so the final document is interview-ready rather than raw.
      </p>
      <a href="/#tool" class="lp-cta">Transcribe an interview →</a>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-steps-section" style="margin: 0 auto 48px;">
      <h2>How it works</h2>
      <div class="lp-steps">
        <div class="lp-step">
          <div class="lp-step-num">01</div>
          <h3>Record or import your interview</h3>
          <p>Load any audio format from any recorder — phone recordings, Zoom exports, dedicated field recorders. The file is opened locally; nothing is sent to a server at any point in the process.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-step">
          <div class="lp-step-num">02</div>
          <h3>Whisper transcribes conversational speech</h3>
          <p>Unlike rule-based transcription tools that struggle with accents and informality, Whisper is trained on the kind of natural, unscripted speech that characterizes real interviews — including cross-talk, hesitation, and domain-specific vocabulary.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-step">
          <div class="lp-step-num">03</div>
          <h3>Export and clean up</h3>
          <p>Edit the transcript before you export — remove filler words, correct misheard proper nouns, and mark speaker turns. Export as plain text to paste into your research tool, report, or analysis software.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-features">
      <h2>Why researchers and journalists use AudioSRT</h2>
      <div class="lp-feature-grid">
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">🔒</div>
          <h3>Source material never uploaded</h3>
          <p>Zero server copy — your audio stays on your device throughout transcription and export. No third-party infrastructure touches the recording.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">🗣️</div>
          <h3>Handles natural conversation</h3>
          <p>Whisper manages overlapping speech, non-native accents, informal register, and domain-specific vocabulary better than consumer voice-memo tools trained on scripted speech.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">✏️</div>
          <h3>Edit before you save</h3>
          <p>Remove filler words, fix misheard names, and annotate speaker turns directly in the editor. The export reflects your edits, not the raw AI output.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">📋</div>
          <h3>Plain text for easy annotation</h3>
          <p>Export as clean plain text and paste directly into Word, Google Docs, Notion, NVivo, or any qualitative analysis tool your workflow already uses.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-cta-section">
      <h2>Transcribe your next interview</h2>
      <p>Free. No account. Your recording stays on your device.</p>
      <a href="/#tool" class="lp-cta">Start transcribing →</a>
    </section>

  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.lp-main { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: #1D1D1F; }
.lp-hero { text-align: center; padding: 80px 20px 60px; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
.lp-badge { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; background: #EEEFFD; color: #6366F1; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 500; padding: 5px 14px; border-radius: 20px; border: 0.5px solid #C7C8F9; margin-bottom: 24px; }
.lp-h1 { font-size: clamp(28px, 4.5vw, 46px); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.8px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.lp-accent { color: #6366F1; }
.lp-intro { font-size: 15px; color: #6E6E73; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 560px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }
.lp-cta { display: inline-block; background: #6366F1; color: #fff; padding: 13px 28px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 500; text-decoration: none; transition: background 0.15s; }
.lp-cta:hover { background: #4F46E5; }
.lp-steps-section { padding: 64px 20px; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; background: #F5F5F7; border-radius: 24px; text-align: center; }
.lp-steps-section h2 { font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 40px; letter-spacing: -0.5px; }
.lp-steps { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 32px; text-align: left; }
@media (max-width: 768px) { .lp-steps { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
.lp-step-num { font-size: 44px; font-weight: 800; color: #EEEFFD; letter-spacing: -2px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.lp-step h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.lp-step p { font-size: 13px; color: #6E6E73; line-height: 1.6; }
.lp-features { padding: 64px 20px; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; }
.lp-features h2 { font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 36px; letter-spacing: -0.5px; }
.lp-feature-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 20px; }
@media (max-width: 600px) { .lp-feature-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
.lp-feature-card { background: #fff; border: 0.5px solid #E5E5E7; border-radius: 14px; padding: 24px; }
.lp-feature-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.lp-feature-card h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.lp-feature-card p { font-size: 13px; color: #6E6E73; line-height: 1.6; }
.lp-cta-section { text-align: center; padding: 64px 20px 80px; }
.lp-cta-section h2 { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.lp-cta-section p { font-size: 14px; color: #6E6E73; margin-bottom: 24px; }
.lp-body { font-size: 14px; color: #3D3D3F; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 14px; }
.lp-detail { max-width: 680px; margin: 64px auto; padding: 0 20px; }
.lp-detail h2 { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.lp-inline-link { color: #6366F1; text-decoration: none; }
.lp-inline-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
